WEBVTT

00:01.901 --> 00:04.637
<i>[cheerful music]</i>

00:04.704 --> 00:11.644
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:12.712 --> 00:14.948
<i>- ♪ Harvey ♪</i>

00:15.014 --> 00:16.683
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:16.750 --> 00:19.018
<i>♪ Harvey ♪</i>

00:19.085 --> 00:24.691
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:24.758 --> 00:26.593
<i>♪ Harvey ♪</i>

00:26.659 --> 00:30.530
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:32.932 --> 00:34.200
- Harvey, I tell ya,

00:34.267 --> 00:36.236
I think about my wedding day
quite often.

00:36.302 --> 00:38.638
{\an3}That was one of the happiest
days of my life.

00:38.705 --> 00:41.107
{\an1}- It's so cool to see
these photos, Dad.

00:41.174 --> 00:43.009
I wish I would've been there.

00:43.076 --> 00:44.911
Hmm.

00:44.978 --> 00:46.179
Dang it!

00:46.246 --> 00:47.580
- I wish you
could've been too, son,

00:47.647 --> 00:49.949
but that would've required
time travel.

00:50.016 --> 00:52.318
- Mom looks like an angel
in her dress.

00:52.385 --> 00:54.087
- I still remember
what she whispered to me

00:54.154 --> 00:55.922
as she walked down the aisle.

00:55.989 --> 00:57.924
"Your fly is down."

00:57.991 --> 00:59.159
- What's this one about?

00:59.225 --> 01:00.527
{\an3}- Oh, ha.
This one was taken

01:00.593 --> 01:02.629
on a small island
in Wet Bark Lake.

01:02.695 --> 01:04.931
We sailed out there
one afternoon

01:04.998 --> 01:06.466
<i>and planted a tree together.</i>

01:06.533 --> 01:08.368
<i>It's where I asked your mother</i>

01:08.435 --> 01:09.502
<i>to marry me.</i>

01:09.569 --> 01:11.938
<i>- Whoa!</i>
<i>What'd she say?</i>

01:12.005 --> 01:14.607
<i>- Well, bud, she said yes.</i>

01:14.674 --> 01:17.310
{\an3}- Man, I can't wait
to get married.

01:17.377 --> 01:18.878
- Really, son?
- Of course!

01:18.945 --> 01:21.581
What little boy doesn't
dream of his wedding day?

01:21.648 --> 01:24.751
- Hey, look,
our marriage certificate.

01:24.818 --> 01:27.153
And it still has
my tearstains.

01:27.220 --> 01:28.855
- Whoa.

01:28.922 --> 01:31.357
This piece of paper
is older than I am.

01:31.424 --> 01:33.993
- That day, we stopped
being two people

01:34.060 --> 01:36.029
and became Miriam and Irving...

01:36.095 --> 01:37.497
- "Borks"?
- What?

01:37.564 --> 01:38.865
- That's what it says.

01:38.932 --> 01:40.667
{\an8}"Miriam and Irving Borks."

01:40.733 --> 01:41.501
{\an8}- What?

01:41.568 --> 01:42.869
I never noticed before.

01:42.936 --> 01:45.238
- You never read
your own marriage certificate?

01:45.305 --> 01:46.873
- I don't know.
It was a big day!

01:46.940 --> 01:49.142
I was busy!
Oh, no.

01:49.209 --> 01:51.611
Does this mean your mother and I
aren't even married?

01:51.678 --> 01:54.080
[stammering]
Have we been living a lie

01:54.147 --> 01:55.715
this entire time?

01:55.782 --> 01:59.052
[sobbing]

01:59.118 --> 02:02.055
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

02:02.121 --> 02:09.262
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:14.934 --> 02:17.003
<i>- There's nothing</i>
<i>to worry about.</i>

02:17.070 --> 02:18.671
<i>You're definitely married.</i>

02:18.738 --> 02:22.008
So what's the problem there,
uh, Mr. Borks?

02:22.075 --> 02:23.176
{\an3}- Ah, that.

02:23.243 --> 02:24.611
Listen, ma'am, and, uh...

02:24.677 --> 02:25.645
Sir?
- [snoring]

02:25.712 --> 02:27.580
[smacking lips]
Hey, hey.

02:27.647 --> 02:29.816
{\an3}- My last name is Beaks,
not Borks.

02:29.883 --> 02:32.685
- Oh, well, that's no problem.

02:32.752 --> 02:33.853
Here.

02:35.421 --> 02:37.790
{\an8}- This--this just
doesn't feel right.

02:37.857 --> 02:39.559
Our wedding day was so perfect.

02:39.626 --> 02:41.594
- Well, why don't you two
get married again?

02:41.661 --> 02:43.530
- What?
- Have another wedding.

02:43.596 --> 02:46.666
{\an1}Not only would you be officially
married as the Beakses,

02:46.733 --> 02:48.902
{\an1}but I'd be there to see
the whole thing.

02:48.968 --> 02:50.703
{\an3}- Harvey.

02:50.770 --> 02:53.239
That's a great idea!

02:53.306 --> 02:55.408
- We're getting married?
Again?

02:55.475 --> 02:57.610
- Honey, it'll be great.
Flowers, cake.

02:57.677 --> 03:00.446
Me in my tux that may
or may not still fit.

03:00.513 --> 03:01.848
[stomach gurgling]

03:01.915 --> 03:04.384
The two of us together.

03:04.450 --> 03:05.685
{\an3}How does
tomorrow sound?

03:05.752 --> 03:07.787
- Um, okay.
- There's a lot to do.

03:07.854 --> 03:11.324
First, I need to choose
a best man.

03:11.391 --> 03:13.326
Harvey?
What do you say?

03:13.393 --> 03:15.628
{\an3}- Me?
Your best man?

03:15.695 --> 03:17.063
- I need someone dependable,

03:17.130 --> 03:18.064
resourceful.

03:18.131 --> 03:19.465
You embody those traits.

03:19.532 --> 03:21.968
I mean, you're literally
taking notes right now.

03:22.035 --> 03:23.403
[pencil scribbling]

03:23.469 --> 03:25.405
- [chuckles]
I'd love to.

03:25.471 --> 03:26.839
I won't let you down, Dad.

03:26.906 --> 03:29.742
I'll be the best
best man ever.

03:29.809 --> 03:31.844
What does the best man do?

03:31.911 --> 03:32.712
- Oh-ho-ho,

03:32.779 --> 03:36.115
he plans the bachelor party.

03:36.182 --> 03:38.918
- Cool, I love planning parties.

03:38.985 --> 03:40.353
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:40.420 --> 03:43.022
{\an3}- Thanks for helping me
with the decorations, Fee.

03:43.089 --> 03:44.290
This is already shaping up

03:44.357 --> 03:45.858
{\an3}to be nicer
than my first wedding.

03:45.925 --> 03:48.061
- I'm surprised you
remember that stuff.

03:48.127 --> 03:49.529
Weren't you and Irving babies?

03:49.596 --> 03:51.097
{\an3}- What?
No, we were married

03:51.164 --> 03:52.498
when we were grown-ups.

03:52.565 --> 03:54.667
{\an1}- So you're saying that you,
Irving, and Harvey

03:54.734 --> 03:56.703
were born at different times?

03:56.769 --> 03:57.837
{\an3}- Yes.

03:57.904 --> 04:00.139
{\an1}- Now I feel bad
for calling Foo a liar.

04:00.206 --> 04:02.575
- I had a life before marriage.

04:02.642 --> 04:05.445
I traveled.
I did cool stuff,

04:05.511 --> 04:07.146
and I had my old band,

04:07.213 --> 04:08.715
Baroness Hag!

04:08.781 --> 04:11.551
{\an1}- You're like
a never ending person.

04:11.618 --> 04:13.453
{\an1}I know how we're gonna spend
your last night

04:13.519 --> 04:14.954
before you get remarried.

04:15.021 --> 04:17.957
- Um, watching Michelle
and Nestflix?

04:18.024 --> 04:18.992
- Hey, Hanzi!

04:19.058 --> 04:21.060
{\an1}You free to watch Michelle
tonight?

04:21.127 --> 04:22.060
[baby babbles]

04:22.128 --> 04:23.830
{\an3}- Oh, sure.

04:23.896 --> 04:27.834
{\an3}Oh, I can tell we're going
to be fast friends.

04:27.900 --> 04:29.502
{\an3}Oh, but not--
ow, no, no.

04:29.569 --> 04:30.770
Hey, hey, don't touch.

04:30.837 --> 04:33.773
{\an1}- Be ready for craziness
at 6:00 p.m.

04:33.840 --> 04:34.574
{\an3}- Yes.

04:34.641 --> 04:36.576
<i>[rock music]</i>

04:36.643 --> 04:38.478
{\an1}- Bachelor party,
bachelor party,

04:38.544 --> 04:39.812
bachelor party!

04:39.879 --> 04:41.047
What's a bachelor party?

04:41.114 --> 04:43.883
{\an3}- You'll just have to wait
and see.

04:43.950 --> 04:45.284
- Excelsior!

04:45.351 --> 04:46.519
[all laughing]

04:46.586 --> 04:49.822
- He truly is
a jolly good fellow.

04:49.889 --> 04:51.457
- Hey, Harvey,
everything's set up

04:51.524 --> 04:55.895
for tomorrow morning,
so tonight we party!

04:55.962 --> 04:58.865
- That's right.
And as the best man--

04:58.931 --> 04:59.799
- What?

04:59.866 --> 05:01.701
- I--I'm the best man?

05:01.768 --> 05:03.069
- But you're a boy.

05:03.136 --> 05:06.105
Now can a <i> boy</i>
really be best man?

05:06.172 --> 05:08.007
{\an1}- Oh, oh, okay, I don't
want to get in--

05:08.074 --> 05:10.343
- Moff, take 'er easy.
Harvey's the perfect best man.

05:10.410 --> 05:11.411
Go on, son.

05:11.477 --> 05:12.779
- Whatever, rules don't matter.

05:12.845 --> 05:13.980
[muttering]
Chaos, whatever.

05:14.047 --> 05:16.449
- Get your sea legs ready,
fellas,

05:16.516 --> 05:19.252
because I rented us
a cruise boat!

05:19.318 --> 05:20.553
{\an3}- Ta-da!

05:20.620 --> 05:22.755
- All aboard.

05:22.822 --> 05:23.823
- All right, guys,

05:23.890 --> 05:25.558
I'd like to propose a toast.

05:25.625 --> 05:28.761
{\an1}To the groom
and a fun wild night.

05:28.828 --> 05:30.229
{\an3}- [laughs]
Whoo-hoo!

05:30.296 --> 05:31.431
- If I was best man,

05:31.497 --> 05:33.499
{\an1}there would have been
fancy drinks.

05:33.566 --> 05:35.401
{\an1}[slurping]

05:35.468 --> 05:37.670
- Land ho!

05:37.737 --> 05:40.506
- It's the island
where I proposed to Miriam.

05:40.573 --> 05:43.476
Look, it's our tree.

05:43.543 --> 05:45.478
[chuckles]

05:45.545 --> 05:49.148
<i>[instrumental music]</i>

05:49.215 --> 05:50.316
[doorbell rings]

05:50.383 --> 05:51.317
- Hey, Fee.

05:51.384 --> 05:52.318
Let me just text Irving

05:52.385 --> 05:53.586
and tell him I'm leaving.

05:53.653 --> 05:54.887
- No, no texting.
Just come with me.

05:54.954 --> 05:57.023
{\an3}Hurry!
Tonight, you don't have

05:57.090 --> 05:58.191
a husband or kids.

05:58.257 --> 05:59.358
{\an1}- Oh.

05:59.425 --> 06:02.128
{\an1}- You're just
Miriam Singlewoman.

06:02.195 --> 06:03.863
- A red carpet.

06:03.930 --> 06:05.098
{\an3}How fancy.

06:05.164 --> 06:07.400
{\an1}- Yeah, I couldn't find
a real red carpet,

06:07.467 --> 06:09.469
{\an1}so I just tossed
a bunch of dirty towels.

06:09.535 --> 06:12.672
{\an1}Here we are,
your luxury party bus.

06:12.739 --> 06:14.207
all: Surprise!

06:14.273 --> 06:15.641
- Oh, hey, kids.

06:15.708 --> 06:17.376
This is so exciting.

06:17.443 --> 06:19.679
{\an3}- I'm going to guide us
to our destination

06:19.746 --> 06:21.981
{\an8}using this GPS.

06:22.048 --> 06:24.183
{\an7}- Piri, those are just
tiny bones.

06:24.250 --> 06:27.720
{\an9}- It says the quickest route
is through the femur.

06:27.787 --> 06:30.590
- So how do you
drive this thing?

06:30.656 --> 06:32.191
Oh, okay.

06:32.258 --> 06:34.694
- Wait, did anybody
cut a window for this?

06:34.761 --> 06:36.462
I can't see any--
[all exclaim]

06:36.529 --> 06:38.598
- Oh, my--
- Okay, this way?

06:39.665 --> 06:42.468
- All right, you crazy dudes.

06:42.535 --> 06:44.203
Welcome to the party.

06:44.270 --> 06:46.005
We've got a...

06:46.072 --> 06:47.073
bounce house!

06:47.140 --> 06:48.808
Slimy string!
- [exclaiming]

06:48.875 --> 06:51.210
- And crazy sick beats.

06:51.277 --> 06:54.013
<i>- ♪ Friendship, friendship</i>
<i>is my friend ♪</i>

06:54.080 --> 06:55.414
<i>♪ Friendship, friendship ♪</i>

06:55.481 --> 06:56.916
{\an1}- Hey, thanks
for the goody bag.

06:56.983 --> 07:00.520
{\an3}- All I got in mine
was 3 nickels and a kazoo.

07:00.586 --> 07:02.488
- Happy bachelor party!

07:02.555 --> 07:04.357
- [blowing kazoo sadly]

07:04.423 --> 07:07.326
<i>[upbeat tinkling music]</i>

07:07.393 --> 07:08.394
[crashing]

07:08.461 --> 07:10.129
- We're here!

07:10.196 --> 07:11.364
- The library.

07:11.430 --> 07:13.733
{\an3}Fee, why did you bring me
to my work?

07:13.800 --> 07:16.502
- You said you liked
playing music, so...

07:16.569 --> 07:19.605
{\an1}I set up a reunion show
for you right now.

07:19.672 --> 07:20.706
- What?

07:20.773 --> 07:23.176
That's awesome!

07:23.242 --> 07:26.746
Oh, but we can't play
loud music in the library.

07:26.813 --> 07:30.683
- We're not technically
gonna be in the library.

07:30.750 --> 07:33.252
We're playing <i> on</i> the library!

07:34.453 --> 07:36.222
<i>[rock music]</i>

07:36.289 --> 07:38.324
- What's up, Littlebark?

07:38.391 --> 07:41.127
Are you ready to rock?

07:41.194 --> 07:44.096
- Oh, hey, Miriam.
You look very cool.

07:44.163 --> 07:46.065
- Oh, hey, Bartleburt.

07:46.132 --> 07:47.133
How's Carol?

07:47.200 --> 07:48.301
- She's okay.

07:48.367 --> 07:50.469
Still with the back problems,
though.

07:50.536 --> 07:52.038
Oh, thanks for asking.

07:52.104 --> 07:54.106
We're excited to see your band.

07:54.173 --> 07:56.075
- I'm just waiting
for the bathroom.

07:56.142 --> 07:58.010
- My band.

07:58.077 --> 08:02.949
Um, Fee, I'm not sure
I can play a show solo.

08:03.015 --> 08:03.749
- Voilà!

08:03.816 --> 08:05.218
both: Surprise!

08:05.284 --> 08:07.053
- Tara, Pooker.

08:07.119 --> 08:08.321
My bandmates!

08:08.387 --> 08:10.156
{\an1}- Oh, we've been waiting
under that blanket

08:10.223 --> 08:11.624
for over four hours.

08:11.691 --> 08:12.758
{\an1}Whoo!
Yeah!

08:12.825 --> 08:14.060
Ladies night!

08:14.126 --> 08:15.995
- Listen, I'm paying
some teenager

08:16.062 --> 08:18.464
to watch my 400 kids until 8:00,

08:18.531 --> 08:20.666
so let's get weird!

08:20.733 --> 08:23.236
- Oh, Fee, this is perfect.

08:23.302 --> 08:24.737
- Ladies and gentlemen,

08:24.804 --> 08:26.439
please welcome to the stage

08:26.505 --> 08:27.840
for one night only,

08:27.907 --> 08:30.710
the super hot
Miriam Singlewoman

08:30.776 --> 08:32.178
and Baroness Hag!

08:32.245 --> 08:36.515
- All right,
let's melt their faces.

08:36.582 --> 08:38.251
- One, two, three, four!

08:38.317 --> 08:41.254
<i>[rock music]</i>

08:41.320 --> 08:47.526
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:47.593 --> 08:50.529
[crowd screaming]

08:50.596 --> 08:55.434
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:55.501 --> 08:59.305
[cheering]

08:59.372 --> 09:01.407
- We love you, Littlebark!

09:01.474 --> 09:03.309
- Hey, everyone, stick around

09:03.376 --> 09:04.577
for the story time reading

09:04.644 --> 09:07.213
of "Detective Dirk
and the Leaky Bucket."

09:07.280 --> 09:10.850
It's suitable for reading levels
8 through 12.

09:10.917 --> 09:12.785
- Hey, put the music back on.

09:12.852 --> 09:15.254
Let's start a pit.
I want to slam dance!

09:15.321 --> 09:20.793
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:20.860 --> 09:21.894
- Warm milk?

09:21.961 --> 09:23.296
No, thank you.

09:23.362 --> 09:24.363
[spitting]

09:24.430 --> 09:25.564
- Hey, Foo, do you think

09:25.631 --> 09:27.366
my dad's having enough fun?

09:27.433 --> 09:28.701
- How could he not?

09:28.768 --> 09:30.202
I'm having fun!

09:30.269 --> 09:31.504
- Yeah.

09:31.570 --> 09:33.105
Yeah, you're right.

09:33.172 --> 09:35.241
This party just needs a boost.

09:35.308 --> 09:38.577
{\an3}Okay, I know some of you guys
wanted a little extra

09:38.644 --> 09:40.012
for tonight's party.

09:40.079 --> 09:42.782
{\an3}So I think you'll like
the special surprise

09:42.848 --> 09:44.684
that's inside this cake.

09:44.750 --> 09:46.819
[both chuckling]

09:46.886 --> 09:49.922
- Um, I don't know
how I feel about this.

09:49.989 --> 09:52.792
- Abracadabra!

09:52.858 --> 09:55.628
I'm the amazing Andy!

09:55.695 --> 09:58.030
{\an3}- Whoo!

09:58.097 --> 10:00.599
- Now get ready for two hours

10:00.666 --> 10:03.269
of uninterrupted...

10:03.336 --> 10:05.838
magic!

10:05.905 --> 10:08.474
- You have got to be kidding me.

10:08.541 --> 10:09.875
- What a waste of cake.

10:09.942 --> 10:10.910
- [harrumphs]

10:10.977 --> 10:13.412
This is unbelievable.

10:13.479 --> 10:15.481
{\an3}- Exactly.

10:15.548 --> 10:16.916
Now pick a card.

10:16.983 --> 10:18.584
- No.
- Any card.

10:18.651 --> 10:19.585
{\an1}- No.

10:19.652 --> 10:20.720
- Any card at all!

10:20.786 --> 10:22.355
- Get away from me!

10:22.421 --> 10:25.358
- [coughing]

10:25.424 --> 10:28.361
{\an3}[retching]

10:33.499 --> 10:35.568
- Okay, I'm ready
to go home now.

10:35.634 --> 10:37.903
- Fellas, come on,
don't be like this.

10:37.970 --> 10:38.938
- Sorry, Irving,

10:39.005 --> 10:42.141
but this party's for babies.

10:42.208 --> 10:43.909
- [sighs]

10:43.976 --> 10:46.912
[laughter]

10:46.979 --> 10:49.181
{\an1}- I got a lot of aggression out
on those drums.

10:49.248 --> 10:52.318
- The library crowd
can really keep a party going.

10:52.385 --> 10:54.920
- I'm so glad
you girls could come out.

10:54.987 --> 10:57.623
Fee, thanks so much
for this party.

10:57.690 --> 10:59.859
- Oh-ho-ho, we're not done yet.

10:59.925 --> 11:02.595
Welcome to the after party!

11:02.661 --> 11:04.897
all: Ooh.

11:04.964 --> 11:07.266
- Your own luxury hotel suite.

11:07.333 --> 11:09.869
{\an3}- We have a bucket
and some ants.

11:09.935 --> 11:11.804
{\an1}- I don't get it.
Are we sleeping outside?

11:11.871 --> 11:13.005
I have sleep apnea.

11:13.072 --> 11:14.940
- This room isn't for sleeping.

11:15.007 --> 11:16.409
It's for destroying!

11:16.475 --> 11:17.943
Like real rock stars.

11:18.010 --> 11:21.747
- Ooh, I've always wanted
to do something like this!

11:21.814 --> 11:22.748
<i>[rock music]</i>

11:22.815 --> 11:23.883
Yeah!

11:23.949 --> 11:25.284
{\an3}- [screams]

11:25.351 --> 11:26.652
- Yahoo!

11:26.719 --> 11:28.154
[all laughing]

11:28.220 --> 11:29.188
- Yeah!

11:29.255 --> 11:30.656
Whoo-hoo!
- [laughing]

11:30.723 --> 11:32.191
- Okay, well, it's getting late.

11:32.258 --> 11:33.526
We're gonna head out.

11:33.592 --> 11:36.228
See you at the wedding tomorrow.

11:36.295 --> 11:37.396
- Tomorrow?

11:37.463 --> 11:41.200
[laughs]
This party is never gonna end!

11:41.267 --> 11:44.203
[grunting]

11:44.270 --> 11:46.038
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:46.105 --> 11:48.741
Whoo-hoo!
Yeah!

11:48.808 --> 11:50.543
Whoo-hoo!
Come on.

11:50.609 --> 11:52.044
- [panting]
- Faster!

11:52.111 --> 11:54.013
- Uh, it's getting pretty late.

11:54.080 --> 11:55.214
Don't you want to

11:55.281 --> 11:56.949
get ready to be married
in the morning?

11:57.016 --> 11:58.417
Maybe check on Michelle?

11:58.484 --> 12:00.419
- I don't want to go back
to normal life.

12:00.486 --> 12:03.622
I want this night
to last forever.

12:03.689 --> 12:04.857
- Forever?

12:04.924 --> 12:06.125
Oh, no.

12:06.192 --> 12:07.927
- Is something wrong, Fee?

12:07.993 --> 12:09.795
- I broke Harvey's mom!

12:09.862 --> 12:11.263
{\an1}- What?

12:11.330 --> 12:12.298
- I just wanted to give her

12:12.364 --> 12:13.666
a night as Miriam Singlewoman,

12:13.732 --> 12:15.067
but I went too far.

12:15.134 --> 12:17.269
She'll never want to go back
to being a mom!

12:17.336 --> 12:18.137
[all gasp]

12:18.204 --> 12:20.172
- I'm just too fun.

12:20.239 --> 12:21.540
- Well, congratulations!

12:21.607 --> 12:23.509
Harvey's gonna live
in a broken home.

12:23.576 --> 12:26.212
{\an1}- He's gonna be
just another statistic.

12:26.278 --> 12:28.781
- I can't let her run away
from her family.

12:28.848 --> 12:31.617
- Whoo!
Whoo-hoo!

12:31.684 --> 12:34.086
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

12:34.153 --> 12:35.888
- Aw, guys, come on.

12:35.955 --> 12:37.857
We can hang
a little longer, right?

12:37.923 --> 12:40.059
- Irving, I only like
to put positive energy

12:40.126 --> 12:42.094
{\an1}out into the world,
so I'll say this:

12:42.161 --> 12:43.295
your party is awful,

12:43.362 --> 12:46.732
{\an1}and I don't want
to be here anymore.

12:46.799 --> 12:48.200
{\an3}- Ah?

12:48.267 --> 12:50.436
- Someone get me out of here!

12:50.503 --> 12:52.238
- I think they're right, Dad.

12:52.304 --> 12:54.306
We should probably go home.

12:54.373 --> 12:55.875
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:55.941 --> 12:59.411
All right, all aboard.

13:01.413 --> 13:02.348
Oh, no.

13:02.414 --> 13:03.549
all: The boat!

13:03.616 --> 13:04.984
- Uh, don't worry.

13:05.050 --> 13:06.218
I can fix this.

13:06.285 --> 13:07.953
- We're stranded!

13:08.020 --> 13:09.655
- I've got everything
under control.

13:09.722 --> 13:11.824
Whoa!

13:11.891 --> 13:14.827
[flames crackling]

13:14.894 --> 13:16.762
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:16.829 --> 13:18.364
[all screaming]

13:18.430 --> 13:20.866
- Oh, no!
Our tree!

13:20.933 --> 13:23.869
[all screaming]

13:23.936 --> 13:24.970
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:25.037 --> 13:26.372
- [screaming]

13:26.438 --> 13:28.107
- [shrieking]

13:28.174 --> 13:29.975
- I'm not the best man.

13:30.042 --> 13:31.977
I'm the worst man.

13:32.044 --> 13:35.381
[all screaming and crying]

13:37.116 --> 13:39.552
[all crying]

13:39.618 --> 13:42.821
- You know, this is probably
the only bachelor party

13:42.888 --> 13:45.291
I'll ever go to.

13:45.357 --> 13:47.560
How very depressing.

13:47.626 --> 13:49.662
- Say, magician,
since it appears

13:49.728 --> 13:52.198
{\an1}we're going to be here
for quite some time,

13:52.264 --> 13:54.233
{\an1}what say you and I
form an alliance

13:54.300 --> 13:56.001
when we begin eating each other?

13:56.068 --> 13:57.369
{\an3}- Oh!

13:57.436 --> 13:58.370
- Harvey?

13:58.437 --> 13:59.672
Where are ya, buddy?

13:59.738 --> 14:02.208
We should start working
on an escape plan.

14:02.274 --> 14:05.444
I mean, not that
I'm not having fun.

14:05.511 --> 14:08.314
<i>[somber music]</i>

14:08.380 --> 14:11.050
Hey, best man, what's wrong?

14:11.116 --> 14:14.620
{\an3}- I wanted to throw you
the best bachelor party ever,

14:14.687 --> 14:16.555
but I totally blew it.

14:16.622 --> 14:18.190
It's terrible.

14:18.257 --> 14:20.059
{\an1}- [scoffs]
What?

14:20.125 --> 14:22.127
People had fun.

14:22.194 --> 14:25.264
[both weeping]

14:25.331 --> 14:26.799
- I ruined everything.

14:26.865 --> 14:29.535
{\an3}I even destroyed
your special tree.

14:29.602 --> 14:32.504
- Well, why don't we...

14:32.571 --> 14:34.340
plant another one?

14:34.406 --> 14:37.343
<i>[gentle instrumental music]</i>

14:37.409 --> 14:43.549
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:43.616 --> 14:45.584
{\an1}Son, I didn't make you
my best man

14:45.651 --> 14:47.987
{\an1}for your ability
to throw bachelor parties.

14:48.053 --> 14:50.923
{\an1}I did it because I wanted
to spend more time with you,

14:50.990 --> 14:53.259
so even though things
went a little crazy,

14:53.325 --> 14:54.660
it doesn't matter.

14:54.727 --> 14:57.696
You will always be my best man.

14:57.763 --> 14:58.797
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:58.864 --> 15:00.232
{\an1}Now we should come up
with a strategy

15:00.299 --> 15:02.268
{\an1}for when everyone starts
eating each other.

15:02.334 --> 15:04.436
I say we target Jeremy first.

15:04.503 --> 15:05.537
- Wait, Dad.

15:05.604 --> 15:07.539
I got us onto this island,

15:07.606 --> 15:10.976
{\an3}so I'm gonna figure out
how to get us off.

15:11.043 --> 15:12.745
Gather the men.

15:12.811 --> 15:14.013
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:14.079 --> 15:16.248
- Whew, how fun.

15:16.315 --> 15:17.383
What's next?

15:17.449 --> 15:19.184
- The next stop is a...

15:19.251 --> 15:20.352
surprise.

15:20.419 --> 15:21.854
Just hop in the tour bus.

15:21.920 --> 15:24.456
- Let's keep this party going!

15:24.523 --> 15:25.457
- Yep.
- Oh!

15:25.524 --> 15:27.559
- I got her!

15:27.626 --> 15:30.029
- Huh?
What's going on?

15:30.095 --> 15:32.064
- You are Mrs. Beaks,

15:32.131 --> 15:33.632
not Miriam Singlewoman!

15:33.699 --> 15:35.934
- What?
- Be gone, evil spirit!

15:36.001 --> 15:38.537
- I'm sorry, but this
is for your own good.

15:38.604 --> 15:40.139
{\an3}I showed you a life
that's too fun,

15:40.205 --> 15:42.641
{\an3}and now you don't want to
get remarried tomorrow.

15:42.708 --> 15:43.909
- What?

15:43.976 --> 15:46.178
Is that what you think
I'm gonna do?

15:46.245 --> 15:49.548
- I just don't want to mess up
my best friend's family.

15:49.615 --> 15:52.217
- Kids, can you hand me
my purse?

15:52.284 --> 15:53.585
- Claire, don't.

15:53.652 --> 15:55.587
{\an1}She's gonna use something
in there to escape.

15:55.654 --> 15:57.623
- But I have to.
She's an adult.

15:57.690 --> 15:59.024
{\an1}- No.
Give me that!

15:59.091 --> 16:00.826
- But it's the rules.
- Claire, let go.

16:00.893 --> 16:02.094
- Guys, guys!

16:02.161 --> 16:03.195
[grunting, blows falling]

16:03.262 --> 16:04.396
- Ow!

16:04.463 --> 16:05.431
[both grunting]

16:05.497 --> 16:06.665
[gasping]

16:08.233 --> 16:09.868
- Huh?

16:09.935 --> 16:11.570
Wedding vows?

16:11.637 --> 16:13.539
- Go ahead and read them.

16:14.773 --> 16:17.609
- "When we started dating,
everyone asked,

16:17.676 --> 16:20.512
"'How'd Irving the nerd
get so lucky?'

16:20.579 --> 16:22.781
"But it turns out,
I was the lucky one,

16:22.848 --> 16:24.850
"because I get to be
with my best friend

16:24.917 --> 16:26.251
"all the time.

16:26.318 --> 16:28.487
"I love how you can never
pick a movie to rent,

16:28.554 --> 16:30.389
"so we just talk all night.

16:30.456 --> 16:32.124
"I love ordering pizza together

16:32.191 --> 16:34.093
"because you burn dinner.

16:34.159 --> 16:36.128
"And I love how you
make up silly stories

16:36.195 --> 16:38.063
for our kids when they
can't go to sleep."

16:38.130 --> 16:39.264
{\an3}- [sobs]

16:39.331 --> 16:41.166
- "I love the life
we have together,

16:41.233 --> 16:44.770
and I wouldn't trade that
for anything in the world."

16:44.837 --> 16:47.773
{\an1}- So will you let me out
so I can get married?

16:47.840 --> 16:48.874
- Yeah.

16:48.941 --> 16:50.776
The cage is just
cardboard anyway.

16:50.843 --> 16:53.312
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:53.379 --> 16:54.413
{\an1}- Oh.

16:54.480 --> 16:56.882
{\an1}Thanks for the amazing party,
Fee.

16:56.949 --> 16:57.983
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:58.050 --> 16:59.318
- Excuse me.

16:59.385 --> 17:01.520
May I please have
everyone's attention?

17:01.587 --> 17:03.055
- Oh, now what?

17:03.122 --> 17:05.758
Still trying to be
the best man?

17:05.824 --> 17:08.527
- No, I'm just trying
to be a man,

17:08.594 --> 17:10.596
and I invite you all
to do the same,

17:10.662 --> 17:11.864
because, men,

17:11.930 --> 17:13.898
we don't need
to <i> be</i> the best.

17:13.965 --> 17:16.201
We just need to <i> do</i> our best...

17:16.268 --> 17:17.502
for the groom,

17:17.569 --> 17:20.172
because he's got
a wedding to attend.

17:20.239 --> 17:22.875
His own.

17:22.941 --> 17:25.277
- Oh, captain!
My captain!

17:25.344 --> 17:26.912
- What?
- Harvey's right.

17:26.979 --> 17:28.981
Let's get Irving
to his wedding!

17:29.048 --> 17:32.651
[all cheering]

17:32.718 --> 17:35.854
<i>[upbeat funky music]</i>

17:35.921 --> 17:40.159
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:40.225 --> 17:42.428
[sawing]

17:42.494 --> 17:45.631
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:45.697 --> 17:47.433
<i>- Oh, yeah.</i>

17:47.499 --> 17:53.372
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:53.439 --> 17:54.473
- All right, men.

17:54.540 --> 17:56.575
Let's get to that wedding!

17:56.642 --> 17:59.144
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:59.211 --> 18:00.512
- The sun is coming up.

18:00.579 --> 18:02.481
{\an1}- Oh, my gosh.
How long have we been hugging?

18:02.548 --> 18:03.615
- The wedding!

18:03.682 --> 18:04.983
<i>[exciting music]</i>

18:05.050 --> 18:06.118
- Oh, crud!

18:06.185 --> 18:09.288
[crowd murmuring]

18:09.354 --> 18:11.957
- Hey, I thought there was
a wedding happening.

18:12.024 --> 18:13.725
Where's the bride
and the groom?

18:13.792 --> 18:15.093
What the heck's going on?

18:15.160 --> 18:16.829
{\an3}- How are we gonna
get down there in time?

18:16.895 --> 18:18.464
- Everyone in the tour bus.

18:18.530 --> 18:19.631
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:19.698 --> 18:21.033
- Sorry, Mrs. Beaks.

18:21.099 --> 18:22.568
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:22.634 --> 18:24.136
- Wait!
Is this safe?

18:24.203 --> 18:26.138
- Yeah, sure, whatever.

18:26.205 --> 18:28.240
[all screaming]

18:28.307 --> 18:29.675
- Keep paddling, fellas!

18:29.741 --> 18:31.276
- Miriam's probably
wondering where I am.

18:31.343 --> 18:33.579
What if she thinks I've gotten
cold feet or something?

18:33.645 --> 18:34.980
What if we never get married?

18:35.047 --> 18:37.483
- Then I'll never be born!
- [screams]

18:37.549 --> 18:38.917
Can't this thing go any faster?

18:38.984 --> 18:41.153
- We're carrying
too much weight!

18:41.220 --> 18:42.621
- Pick a card, any card.

18:42.688 --> 18:44.356
{\an1}- [exclaims]
There!

18:44.423 --> 18:46.692
Now row with all your might!

18:46.758 --> 18:50.262
[all screaming]

18:50.329 --> 18:52.431
- Claire, Piri!
You two are on makeup duty.

18:52.498 --> 18:53.899
- Don't worry, Mrs. Beaks.

18:53.966 --> 18:56.468
- I've only ruined
four of my dolls this way.

18:56.535 --> 18:58.003
- These branches!

18:58.070 --> 18:59.938
Ow!
Would you quit it?

19:00.005 --> 19:02.040
{\an3}- This is how
I relieve stress, Dade.

19:02.107 --> 19:03.642
- [grunting]

19:03.709 --> 19:05.410
{\an1}Oh, no.
What is that?

19:05.477 --> 19:06.411
{\an1}[grunts]

19:06.478 --> 19:09.414
[all screaming]

19:09.481 --> 19:14.753
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:14.820 --> 19:17.623
[crowd murmuring]

19:17.689 --> 19:18.624
- This is ridiculous.

19:18.690 --> 19:19.858
Another five minutes,

19:19.925 --> 19:21.393
and I'm probably
just gonna leave.

19:21.460 --> 19:22.594
[all panting]

19:22.661 --> 19:24.196
[exclaiming]

19:24.263 --> 19:26.198
- [panting]

19:26.265 --> 19:28.066
- Dad, your tux!

19:28.133 --> 19:30.802
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:30.869 --> 19:32.204
- Is everyone okay?

19:32.271 --> 19:33.505
- I got some splinters.

19:33.572 --> 19:34.640
- There's no time for that!

19:34.706 --> 19:35.841
Here's your dress, Miriam.

19:35.908 --> 19:37.042
I cut it into smaller pieces

19:37.109 --> 19:38.911
so you can put it on faster.

19:38.977 --> 19:41.547
- Fee, you're a genius.

19:41.613 --> 19:43.448
- Hurry!
We need more tape!

19:43.515 --> 19:45.584
- I can't find the end.

19:45.651 --> 19:49.321
[crowd murmuring]

19:49.388 --> 19:50.389
- Well, all right, then.

19:50.455 --> 19:52.024
I'm going home.
- Wait!

19:52.090 --> 19:52.824
[all grunt]

19:52.891 --> 19:54.092
- I'm here!

19:54.159 --> 19:55.827
Don't start the wedding
without me!

19:55.894 --> 19:56.828
[crowd gasps]

19:56.895 --> 20:00.032
[all panting]

20:00.098 --> 20:06.672
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:06.738 --> 20:08.440
- Oh, there you are, Hanzi.

20:08.507 --> 20:09.808
- Uh-huh.

20:09.875 --> 20:12.277
{\an1}- Good.
We're ready to start.

20:12.344 --> 20:13.445
- But where's Miriam?

20:13.512 --> 20:16.448
<i>[dramatic instrumental music]</i>

20:16.515 --> 20:18.417
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:18.483 --> 20:21.620
<i>[Mendelssohn's "Midsummer</i>
<i>Night's Dream: Wedding March"]</i>

20:21.687 --> 20:25.257
<i>[upbeat organ music]</i>

20:25.324 --> 20:27.092
She's perfect.

20:27.159 --> 20:34.099
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:36.969 --> 20:38.704
You look beautiful, sweetie.

20:38.770 --> 20:41.673
- Aw, and you look so handsome.

20:41.740 --> 20:42.975
- Let's get married.

20:43.041 --> 20:44.676
- I can't do this.

20:44.743 --> 20:45.844
Take her now.

20:45.911 --> 20:47.613
{\an1}- Hanzi?
What's wrong?

20:47.679 --> 20:49.681
- Your daughter is...

20:49.748 --> 20:51.016
a lot.

20:51.083 --> 20:54.353
I need to be secluded
for several days.

20:54.419 --> 20:55.354
- Wait, what?

20:55.420 --> 20:57.122
- Good-bye now.

20:57.189 --> 20:59.324
{\an1}- Who's going to officiate
the wedding?

20:59.391 --> 21:00.325
- I'll do it!

21:00.392 --> 21:01.693
- You're a registered officiant?

21:01.760 --> 21:02.694
- Of course.

21:02.761 --> 21:03.795
What little boy isn't

21:03.862 --> 21:06.765
{\an8}a registered wedding officiant?

21:06.832 --> 21:08.667
Okay, uh...

21:08.734 --> 21:11.203
this is more complicated
than I remember.

21:11.269 --> 21:12.304
How about this?

21:12.371 --> 21:13.639
Married!
Kiss!

21:13.705 --> 21:16.642
[cheers and applause]

21:16.708 --> 21:19.478
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:19.544 --> 21:24.483
I now pronounce you
Mr. and Mrs. Beaks.

21:24.549 --> 21:26.818
- Let's get this party started!

21:26.885 --> 21:29.821
<i>[upbeat pop music]</i>

21:29.888 --> 21:33.091
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:33.158 --> 21:34.693
- You're a really lucky guy.

21:34.760 --> 21:36.361
{\an1}[crying]
You treat her right.

21:36.428 --> 21:41.366
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:41.433 --> 21:43.168
[camera shutter clicks]

21:43.235 --> 21:44.569
- There we go.

21:44.636 --> 21:45.704
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:45.771 --> 21:48.306
Perfect.

21:48.373 --> 21:50.942
{\an1}Congratulations,
Mr. and Mrs. Beaks.

21:51.009 --> 21:53.378
- Thanks, best man.

21:53.445 --> 21:55.514
- Yes, what a wedding.

21:55.580 --> 21:59.117
It was amazing!

21:59.184 --> 22:00.886
- Please, leave our home.
